notes: 7 moons (Hecate, Math Mathonwy, O-Kuni-Nushi, Isis, Soma, Mon, Sehaine/Eilistraee)

name: Winterlight
notes: Major IEN port and elven world

name: Arborianna
source: Evermeet: Island of the Elves p.87
creator: TSR

name: Talangran
notes: This planet holds the Talangran Empire, a spelljamming aware groundling nation with superior technology and a thirst for Elven slaves.

name: Ghenrek IV / Gaia
notes: Home of Wilderlands of High Fantasy setting

name: Aurel
notes: Gate to elemental plane of fire

name: The Heart
notes: Heartspace's enormous primary "beats" (giving the sphere its name), pulsing from dark to light slowly within the space of about ten minutes. It is a deep red star, otherwise as typical as any other. This sun is one of the largest of all the spheres.

name: Xixchil Homeworld
notes: The Xixchil's homeworld is a live world with many predators.

name: Blacksea
notes: 4 moons (Dead Reef, Orb, The Web, Elamshin D'lil Yorn)

name: World of the Lost Ones
source: MC7 Monstrous Compendium Spelljammer Appendix. Dragon #350, page 59.

name: Parcelius
notes: likely a fairly cosmopolitan, spelljammer-aware world.

name: Sydia
notes: Paladin Orders that hold the Spelljammer as a thing of whoreship

name: Tellene
notes: The Kingdoms of Kalamar campaign setting.

name: Ringling
description: An Air-body primary, it still provides a decent amount of light to see through some mechanism deep within it.

name: Désolée
description: A flat Earth-body, it rotates its faces towards the sun so it still has a day and night cycle, though there are communities in perpetual twilight on the sides (which are quite thin). Center for the most anti-clown rebellion in the system.

name: Barnoom
description: A Torus-shaped Earth-body, it lies perpendicular to Ringling so that the inside of the Torus gets very little light. This functions as equivalent to an Underdark and is the primary headquarters of the Space Clowns, centered in their capital: The Dark Carnival, which floats menacingly in the center of the Torus.  Its moon is Bay-Lee [Barnum & Bailey]. A Size A Air-body with a Water-type ring around it. The habitable side of the ring faces away from Barnoom. Populations live on islands floating in the ring. Each island has a "temple" dedicated to the Space Clowns, on which they yearly give sacrifices to their Clown Gods. Each temple resembles a cross between a circus tent and a Ziggurat.
